OL,3,CAustralian cockroach kingpin caught
OL,4,Cwith more than 100,000 illegal insects
OL,6,FMore than 100,000 live cockroaches
OL,7,Fhave been seized from a single breeder
OL,8,Fin Australia in what officials say is
OL,9,Fthe country's largest-ever
OL,10,Fconfiscation of exotic invertebrates.
OL,12,FThe haul of Madagascar hissing
OL,13,Fcockroaches and dubia cockroaches,
OL,14,Fwhich are illegal to keep in
OL,15,FAustralia, was seized in May from a
OL,16,Fcommercial breeder in Bathurst,
OL,17,FAustralia's Department of Climate
OL,18,FChange, Energy, Environment and Water
OL,19,Fsaid on Friday.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/6
