OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1780686674
OL,3,CAustralian cockroach kingpin caught
OL,4,Cwith more than 100,000 illegal insects
OL,6,FCockroaches thrive in Australia's
OL,7,Fsubtropical climate, and the country
OL,8,Fis home to hundreds of native species.
OL,10,FBathurst snake catcher Stefanie Lesser
OL,11,Ftold Australia's ABC News that the
OL,12,Flarger exotic species were probably
OL,13,Fstolen to be sold as reptile food, as
OL,14,Ftheir size meant fewer insects were
OL,15,Fneeded to feed lizards.
OL,17,FOfficials urged pet owners to use
OL,18,Fcrickets or wood roaches to feed their
OL,19,Flizards instead.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
